From: Riajul Islam <kmriajulislami@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 20 Feb 2026 09:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: restore local-first project experience for v0.1.15

Disables cloud workspaces as default destination to preserve the original
local-first experience which is better suited for self-hosted deployments
and agent orchestration workflows.

Changes:
- Change default destination from /workspaces/create to /onboarding
- This ensures users see onboarding or go directly to their projects
- Prevents automatic redirect to cloud workspaces UI

These changes maintain the preferred local project workflow for
self-hosted installations where users manage local projects rather
than cloud workspaces.
---
 frontend/src/pages/ui-new/RootRedirectPage.tsx | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/frontend/src/pages/ui-new/RootRedirectPage.tsx b/frontend/src/pages/ui-new/RootRedirectPage.tsx
index 1eaa23b7..8f5c4b16 100644
--- a/frontend/src/pages/ui-new/RootRedirectPage.tsx
+++ b/frontend/src/pages/ui-new/RootRedirectPage.tsx
@@ -4,7 +4,7 @@ import { useUserSystem } from '@/components/ConfigProvider';
 import { getFirstProjectDestination } from '@/lib/firstProjectDestination';
 import { useOrganizationStore } from '@/stores/useOrganizationStore';

-const DEFAULT_DESTINATION = '/workspaces/create';
+const DEFAULT_DESTINATION = '/onboarding';

 export function RootRedirectPage() {
   const { config, loading, loginStatus } = useUserSystem();
